# GDS Website Builder — GOV.UK Design System v6.1.0

GOV.UK Frontend v6.1.0 provides the CSS, JS, and component patterns for UK government services. All output uses plain HTML with `govuk-*` CSS classes. **No Nunjucks** — generate clean HTML.

Install: `npm install govuk-frontend@6.1.0`

In your HTML `<head>`:
```html
<link rel="stylesheet" href="/govuk-frontend/dist/govuk/govuk-frontend.min.css">
```

Before `</body>`:
```html
<script type="module">
  import { initAll } from '/govuk-frontend/dist/govuk/govuk-frontend.min.js'
  initAll()
</script>
```

---

## CRITICAL: v6.1.0 Breaking Changes from v5.x

1. **Header is a `<div>`, NOT a `<header>`** — use `<div class="govuk-header">`
2. **Header uses the new Tudor Crown SVG logotype** — a single combined SVG (viewBox `0 0 324 60`, width 162, height 30). Do NOT use the old separate crown + text approach.
3. **Service name is NO LONGER in the header** — use the separate `govuk-service-navigation` component below the header instead
4. **Footer is a `<div>`, NOT a `<footer>`** — use `<div class="govuk-footer">`
5. **Footer has a standalone Tudor Crown SVG** — crown-only (viewBox `0 0 64 60`, width 32, height 30) with `role="presentation"`
6. **Footer has an inline OGL licence logo SVG** — replaces old image reference
7. **Phase banner wording** — "This is a new service. Help us improve it and give your feedback by email."

