## Accessibility Rules (WCAG 2.1 AA)
1. Every input/textarea/select must have a `<label>` with matching `for`/`id`
2. Group related inputs in `<fieldset>` + `<legend>`
3. All hint/error IDs must be in `aria-describedby` on the input
4. Error messages must start with `<span class="govuk-visually-hidden">Error:</span>`
5. Use `autocomplete` on personal data fields
6. Skip link `<a href="#main-content">` must be first focusable element
7. `<main id="main-content">` required
8. Page title format: `[Page title] – [Service name] – GOV.UK`
9. Error page title: prefix with `Error: `
10. Never `outline: none` without replacement focus style

